The paper deals with the effects of noise on computations of a Turing machine, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR). The construction of a Turing machine that can resist bursts of faults also involves the study of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) and distributed computing (cs.DC). Finally, the simulation of fault-free machines under certain conditions is a problem in software engineering (cs.SE).
